1
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:16,067
I know you're not
used to fights.

2
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:18,700
You've hated it ever
since we were young.

3
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:20,767
And now that we're together,

4
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,733
I'm dragging you into a mess.

5
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:26,233
Amanda, stop thinking about
negative things, please.

6
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:28,167
We've wanted to make
a fire, right?

7
00:00:28,233 --> 00:00:29,800
We might succeed
in making it today.

8
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:31,633
Take your medicine first.

9
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,167
So you'll recover fully.

10
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:37,133
I'm not done with Amanda yet.

11
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,367
I still have a lot of things
that I want you to do.

12
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:40,567
There it is.

13
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:41,300
I can almost see it.
I can already see the ember.

14
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:50,133
May you always be
protected from any harm.

15
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:55,967
I pray that you come
back with us alive.

16
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:59,967
I met a rice cakes
supplier on the street.

17
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:02,733
I told her I would sell it.

18
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,367
I want to support
my child this time.

19
00:01:05,433 --> 00:01:09,600
I can feel in my heart
that my daughter is alive.

20
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:11,200
The music seems
to get faster.

21
00:01:11,267 --> 00:01:11,833
What?

22
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:12,900
It's getting faster.

23
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:13,633
Really?

24
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:15,267
Yes. It's fast now.

25
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:16,667
The music is fast.

26
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,767
I'm sorry.

27
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,833
I'm sorry, Yen.

28
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:06,200
Sorry, I'm not taking
advantage of you.

29
00:02:06,267 --> 00:02:08,100
That was my first kiss.

30
00:02:10,867 --> 00:02:11,667
Wow.

31
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,333
I'm embarrassed.

32
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:20,400
It's only now that I have
experienced those things.

33
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,033
Well,

34
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,300
I hope I did not disappoint.

35
00:02:29,767 --> 00:02:31,300
You're at it again.

36
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:35,267
Well, Yen...

37
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:37,367
I'm not sorry for kissing you.

38
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:41,433
Because that's what I feel.

39
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:46,200
But perhaps I took advantage
of our situation.

40
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:49,067
And for that, I ask
for your forgiveness.

41
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:53,267
You did nothing wrong, Red.

42
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:54,733
I was just surprised.

43
00:02:58,667 --> 00:03:00,533
I'll go ahead.

44
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:01,800
It's late.

45
00:03:01,867 --> 00:03:03,200
I'll go to sleep now.

46
00:04:59,367 --> 00:05:00,500
Red!

47
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,400
Red, wake up!

48
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:02,700
Red!

49
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:04,667
Red, you have
to fight, Red!

50
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,133
You will going to hug my mom.

51
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:12,400
Red, we're still going home!

52
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:15,267
Red!

53
00:05:36,867 --> 00:05:38,133
I'm so lucky.

54
00:05:39,867 --> 00:05:40,700
You did not only save me.

55
00:05:40,767 --> 00:05:42,367
I was also your
first kiss.

56
00:05:44,433 --> 00:05:47,200
Thank you for staying
by my side.

57
00:05:48,467 --> 00:05:51,233
I will never leave you too.

58
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:54,900
And I will never let
the two of us be separated.

59
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:24,367
Red?

60
00:07:25,067 --> 00:07:25,900
Red?

61
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:27,933
Red, wake up.

62
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,700
Oh, breakfast in bed.

63
00:07:36,767 --> 00:07:39,533
At your service, Sir.

64
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,067
I even took the
bones out for you.

65
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,967
Okay.

66
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,533
You cooked it so well.

67
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,667
Of course.

68
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:55,133
Why?

69
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,700
Is there fish bone?

70
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,567
There it is.

71
00:07:58,633 --> 00:07:59,733
I got it.

72
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,600
How did that happen?

73
00:08:00,667 --> 00:08:02,400
I took all the
fish bones out.

74
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:06,800
I was just kidding.

75
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:09,067
Hey! You always do that.

76
00:08:13,967 --> 00:08:15,600
I suddenly miss my mom.

77
00:08:19,933 --> 00:08:22,433
She used to prepare
breakfast for me too.

78
00:08:23,933 --> 00:08:27,867
And she always reminds
me not to skip breakfast.

79
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,500
My mom is a good cook.

80
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:36,100
She loves experimenting
with food.

81
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:37,767
And then,

82
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:39,467
my brother and I
are her food critics.

83
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:45,533
You know...

84
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:48,033
mothers are always like that.

85
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:49,867
They always take care of us.

86
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:50,800
Right?

87
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:53,067
Yes,

88
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,167
I know.

89
00:08:57,533 --> 00:09:00,767
I love my mom so much.

90
00:09:03,967 --> 00:09:06,267
Even if...

91
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:08,300
even if she has changed,

92
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:12,500
I still try to understand her.

93
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:20,767
I can understand her until
she's ready to let go.

94
00:09:25,167 --> 00:09:27,233
Thank you for the updates.

95
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,333
Okay.

96
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,733
So what did they say?

97
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:40,800
Talk to me, Victor!

98
00:09:40,867 --> 00:09:42,000
Come on.

99
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:44,000
What's going on?

100
00:09:44,067 --> 00:09:46,733
Can we still count on them?

101
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,167
The search and rescue
operations cannot go on

102
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:51,033
indefinitely searching
for survivors.

103
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:52,667
That's why they can't say

104
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:55,300
how long they
will keep searching.

105
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:56,000
I don't understand.

106
00:09:56,067 --> 00:09:57,833
So that's it?

107
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,733
How about our son?

108
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,967
We can hire someone
who will find him.

109
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:06,100
I don't care if we bleed
money in finding him.

110
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:09,333
I don't understand why
this is happening to us!

111
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,800
We're good people!

112
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:14,700
Rina,

113
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:18,100
actions speak
louder than words.

114
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:19,300
Sorry?

115
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:22,967
What are you trying to say?

116
00:10:23,033 --> 00:10:25,533
What was Zandro doing here?

117
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,500
I saw you last night
talking to him.

118
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:28,133
What were you talking about?

119
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:31,500
I know you two are
doing something shady.

120
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:34,067
So if you really want
good karma,

121
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,633
leave Amanda alone.

122
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:37,333
Stop getting back at her.

123
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,033
How can I leave her alone?

124
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,167
Tell me, Victor.

125
00:10:40,233 --> 00:10:43,633
Because I can still
feel the pain!

126
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:46,600
Like it was only yesterday
when our son died!

127
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:47,900
Rina,

128
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:50,267
it's painful for me too.

129
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:52,900
If you're hurting too,
you should think about me.

130
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:55,000
Not that woman!

131
00:10:55,067 --> 00:10:57,833
She deserves what
is happening to her!

132
00:10:57,900 --> 00:11:01,100
She should have
a miserable life!

133
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,933
Can you hear that?

134
00:11:25,767 --> 00:11:27,200
We're almost there.

135
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,067
Yen, there is a waterfall!

136
00:11:51,133 --> 00:11:52,800
It's so beautiful! Come on, Yen!

137
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:35,833
We don't need to wait for
the rain to get water.

138
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:37,667
We already have a source.

139
00:13:55,133 --> 00:13:56,733
Yen, come on!

140
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,700
Enjoy yourself.

141
00:13:57,767 --> 00:13:59,867
I'll just get our container

142
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:02,400
so we can bring water
back to our shelter.

143
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,133
Yen, I'm having cramps!

144
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:04,900
What?

145
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,233
Yen, it hurts! Help me!

146
00:14:06,300 --> 00:14:07,400
- Wait!
 - Yen!

147
00:14:08,667 --> 00:14:09,767
- Yen!
- Hold on!

148
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,367
Yen, help me!

149
00:14:13,433 --> 00:14:14,733
It hurts!

150
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,167
- Wait, wait, wait!
- Yen, it hurts!

151
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,133
Yen, help me!

152
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,033
Yen!

153
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,633
Are you okay?

154
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:25,667
See?

155
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:28,967
- Was I good? Was it good?
- It's not funny!

156
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:30,067
You don't want to join me.

157
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:33,167
That's the only way
I could think of.

158
00:14:33,233 --> 00:14:34,533
Whatever.

159
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,200
But you have to admit,

160
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:38,800
you were convinced even if
I wasn't good at acting.

161
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:39,700
Was it like this?

162
00:14:41,233 --> 00:14:42,600
Stop it, Red.

163
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:45,233
Go on. I'm gonna leave you here.

164
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:47,000
Come on, don't be mad at me.

165
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:48,433
I'm sorry.

166
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,900
You should smile now.

167
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:52,933
Didn't I tell you that you're
prettier when you're smiling?

168
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:13,400
Red!

169
00:16:20,767 --> 00:16:22,067
Red, look.

170
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:25,867
I found this in the luggage.

171
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:28,733
We can use this as your bandage.

172
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:31,900
It will be a waste if
you use it as a bandage.

173
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:33,567
I think it will fit you.

174
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:36,500
You want me to wear this
gown on this island?

175
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:37,667
Come on.

176
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:38,600
Why not?

177
00:16:39,633 --> 00:16:41,167
We're the only ones here.

178
00:16:42,167 --> 00:16:44,867
Have you tried wearing
something like this?

179
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:46,733
I haven't.

180
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,967
I don't have money for it.

181
00:16:48,033 --> 00:16:49,733
And I don't have a reason
to wear something like that.

182
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,333
Yen, all the more
you should do it.

183
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:55,067
Make the most out
of what we can enjoy.

184
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:02,400
What's in your pocket?

185
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:05,200
- Nothing.
- Let me see.

186
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:06,233
It's nothing.

187
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:06,967
Let me see. You have
something in your pocket.
- Nothing!
- There is!

188
00:17:08,867 --> 00:17:09,767
Let me see.
Show it to me!

189
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:12,233
- Stop!
 - Let me see.

190
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:13,200
It's nothing.

191
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:16,267
Where did you get this wound?

192
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:17,400
It's just a minor cut.

193
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:18,367
It's okay.

194
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:36,467
It's now healed.

195
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,500
Why?

196
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,633
Why aren't you saying anything?

197
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:56,167
My mom used to do that too.

198
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:04,233
When we get hurt from playing,
she kisses our wounds too.

199
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:05,267
She hugs us...

200
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:07,933
she kisses us...

201
00:18:09,833 --> 00:18:13,600
and everything
will be all right.

202
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:18,100
I don't get you.

203
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:21,100
Whenever you remember your mom,

204
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:27,067
you both look happy and sad.

205
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:30,900
It's like you want
to say something.

206
00:18:32,533 --> 00:18:34,633
It's okay. I'm here.

207
00:18:34,700 --> 00:18:37,100
You can tell me anything.

208
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:42,367
Ever since my older
brother died,

209
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,833
everything in our family
has changed.

210
00:18:49,467 --> 00:18:51,100
Especially...

211
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,633
my mom.

212
00:18:56,833 --> 00:18:59,000
Why did your brother die?

213
00:19:02,167 --> 00:19:04,133
He didn't just die.

214
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:07,200
He was killed.

215
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:21,767
Sorry, Red. I didn't know.

216
00:19:23,433 --> 00:19:25,200
But...

217
00:19:25,267 --> 00:19:26,933
Sorry.

218
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,067
It's okay.

219
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:32,000
I seldom talk about it.

220
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:34,400
Because...

221
00:19:36,933 --> 00:19:38,100
it's painful.

222
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:41,533
It still hurts whenever
I remember that.

223
00:19:43,533 --> 00:19:46,767
Who killed your brother?

224
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:59,033
Red, it's okay.

225
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:00,033
It's okay.

226
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:04,667
It's okay.

227
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,700
I'm sorry.

228
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:13,667
It's still hard for me
to talk about it.

229
00:20:15,733 --> 00:20:16,867
It's okay.

230
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:22,133
I won't force you to talk about
it if you're not ready yet.

231
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:25,067
Thank you.

232
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,233
Just remember,

233
00:20:28,300 --> 00:20:30,367
I'm always here for you.

234
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,067
Dindi!

235
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,267
- Amanda.
- You forgot your food.

236
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:47,000
You were in a hurry.

237
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:49,033
Oh, yeah. I'm sorry.

238
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:51,400
It's my contract
renewal today.

239
00:20:51,467 --> 00:20:54,600
I can't work
without my contract.

240
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:57,600
I might get higher
pay this time.

241
00:20:57,667 --> 00:21:00,033
- I hope so.
- I can save some money now.

242
00:21:00,100 --> 00:21:04,867
We can start a small
business for you.

243
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:06,433
Thank you, Dindi.

244
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,300
I'm also thinking
about that.

245
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,867
Because I'm not sure if there's
someone who will still hire me.

246
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:14,433
So I should really think
of putting up a business.

247
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,200
Just a small business, right?

248
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:18,267
I don't want to be
a burden to you.

249
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,967
Don't worry, Amanda.

250
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:22,433
- All our plans will happen.
 - I really hope so.

251
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,767
We just have to be hardworking
and persistent

252
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:26,467
along with prayers.

253
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:28,067
- Go on.
- Thank you, Amanda.

254
00:21:29,033 --> 00:21:31,800
Ma'am Josie, good morning.

255
00:21:31,867 --> 00:21:32,667
I'm ready.

256
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:35,267
I'm ready to
sign my contract.

257
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:37,300
I'm sorry, Dindi.

258
00:21:37,367 --> 00:21:39,667
Your contract
won't be renewed.

259
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:44,167
What?

260
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:46,500
Why?

261
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:48,700
I have a good record.

262
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:51,500
And did I fail
on something?

263
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:53,967
Did I do something
wrong, Ma'am?

264
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:54,867
It's not like that.

265
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:57,867
But we're cutting
down on our staff.

266
00:21:57,933 --> 00:22:01,567
But why me?

267
00:22:01,633 --> 00:22:03,933
It's unfair.

268
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,900
You didn't remove those
who have bad records.

269
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:11,400
Why are you firing someone
like me who has a good record?

270
00:22:11,467 --> 00:22:12,900
What's your basis?

271
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,867
Why are you firing me?

272
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:16,233
That is management's
decision.

273
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:18,700
We can't do anything about it.

274
00:22:18,767 --> 00:22:21,000
Ma'am Josie!

275
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:23,367
Ma'am, excuse me.

276
00:22:23,433 --> 00:22:26,167
Are you firing her
just like that?

277
00:22:26,233 --> 00:22:31,533
Why did you tell
her only now?

278
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:36,400
You should have told her
before her contract ended.

279
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:41,433
So she'd have time to
look for a new job.

280
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,100
You made her believe that
her contract would be renewed.

281
00:22:43,167 --> 00:22:44,700
Wait, who are you?

282
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:46,633
Why do you stick your nose
into someone else's business?

283
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,767
Do you want me to call security?

284
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:49,567
Guard!
Ma'am...

285
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,500
Guard! Come here!

286
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:52,567
Ma'am, is it wrong to ask?
I just asked a question.

287
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:54,067
Did you really have
to call the guard?

288
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:55,433
Yes, Ma'am? What's going on?

289
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,433
Escort them outside
the building.

290
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:57,600
She's making a scene here!

291
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,100
- What?
 - Drive them away!

292
00:22:59,167 --> 00:23:00,300
We're not here
for trouble!

293
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:02,833
We're not making a scene!

294
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,667
You're unbelievable!

295
00:23:04,733 --> 00:23:06,067
Ma'am Josie!

296
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:09,333
You're heartless!

297
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:12,900
Have you ever thought
about if she has food to eat?

298
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:14,833
Get out of here, or I'll
call the cops on you!

299
00:23:14,900 --> 00:23:16,367
We're not afraid of cops!

300
00:23:16,433 --> 00:23:17,233
Get them out of here!

301
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:19,300
We're not doing
anything wrong!

302
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:21,233
Think about Yenyen.

303
00:23:21,300 --> 00:23:22,333
You might end up in jail.

304
00:23:22,433 --> 00:23:24,233
Let's just go.

305
00:23:25,433 --> 00:23:26,967
Yes! It's done!

306
00:23:28,133 --> 00:23:29,600
My wounds are all worth it.

307
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:31,933
I made something beautiful.

308
00:23:43,433 --> 00:23:44,800
Yen!

309
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:45,867
Red!

310
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,200
Red...

311
00:23:57,267 --> 00:24:00,000
You're right. The gown fits me.

312
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,000
You look good in it.

313
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:06,600
But I think
something is missing.

314
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:07,567
What is it?

315
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:13,633
Is that the thing
you're hiding from me?

316
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,633
Yes.

317
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:18,300
I made this for you.

318
00:24:19,733 --> 00:24:21,367
Here's mine.
I'm already wearing it.

319
00:24:24,067 --> 00:24:26,067
I made this for you...

320
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:32,300
to remind us that we will,

321
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:36,300
never leave each other.

322
00:24:44,233 --> 00:24:47,900
With all the things that
happened to us on this island,

323
00:24:47,967 --> 00:24:50,600
I only have one feeling.

324
00:24:54,267 --> 00:24:58,400
I promise upon the trees...

325
00:25:00,033 --> 00:25:01,700
the plants...

326
00:25:03,133 --> 00:25:04,567
the sea...

327
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:06,800
the rain...

328
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,767
that...

329
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,767
these sea shells would,

330
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:18,167
bind us together...

331
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,433
forever.

332
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:34,867
What will you do first
when we get back to Manila?

333
00:25:34,933 --> 00:25:37,400
I will hug my parents.

334
00:25:37,500 --> 00:25:39,033
I will introduce you to them.

335
00:25:39,867 --> 00:25:41,300
We're not going to be separated.

336
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:43,267
I will hug my mom too.

337
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:46,400
And I will kiss her many times.

338
00:25:46,467 --> 00:25:48,067
And then I'll go back to school.

339
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:50,400
Because I want to be a lawyer.

340
00:25:50,467 --> 00:25:53,833
I want to help the poor,

341
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:56,900
who doesn't get justice
like my mom.

342
00:25:56,967 --> 00:26:00,900
Was your mom jailed
even if she's innocent?

343
00:26:00,967 --> 00:26:03,000
What's her case?

344
00:26:03,067 --> 00:26:07,167
And who put her in jail?
